    "description": "Clethra scabra is a shrub or tree growing in habitats from 950 to 2,500 m in altitude, native to the eastern Andes and adjacent montane woodlands and Chaco of Brazil, Bolivia, Paraguay, and northwest Argentina. It is able to reach 25 m (82 ft) in height, and is known to flower during March. It bears simple ovate to elongate and slightly obovate leaves 8 to 10 cm in length and 4 to 6 cm in width. These leaves tend to bear stellate hairs, and have prominent veins upon their abaxial face.",
